VALUES
(43, 7, 22, 3, 12, 3, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Circumcision Practices', 'Both passages emphasize the practice of circumcision on the eighth day, highlighting its significance in Jewish law. John references the tradition established by Moses, linking it to the command in Leviticus.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 22, 1, 17, 10, 14, 'circumcision', 'Circumcision and Covenant Connection', 'This connection highlights the significance of circumcision as a covenantal sign in both passages. John 7:22 refers to the practice of circumcision, which is established in Genesis 17:10-14 as a token of God''s covenant.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 22, 45, 4, 9, 11, 'circumcision; (not because it is of Moses, but of the fathers;)', 'Circumcision and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the significance of circumcision as a sign of faith and righteousness. Both passages emphasize that righteousness is attributed to faith, regardless of physical circumcision.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 22, 48, 3, 17, 17, NULL, 'Covenant and Law Connection', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the law given through Moses and the covenant established by God. Both passages emphasize the continuity of God''s promises despite the introduction of the law.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 23, 43, 5, 14, 16, 'made a man every whit whole', 'Sabbath Healing Controversy', 'Both passages emphasize the act of making a man whole on the Sabbath, highlighting the conflict between Jesus'' healing and Jewish law. The anger of the Jews in both instances stems from their interpretation of Sabbath observance.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 23, 40, 12, 5, 5, 'sabbath day', 'Sabbath Observance and Exceptions', 'This connection highlights the theme of Sabbath observance and exceptions made for important actions. Both passages emphasize the idea that certain activities, like circumcision and temple work, are permissible on the Sabbath.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 23, 40, 12, 2, 2, NULL, 'Sabbath Law and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the conflict over actions deemed unlawful on the Sabbath. John 7:23 discusses healing on the Sabbath, while Matthew 12:2 addresses the disciples'' actions that the Pharisees consider unlawful.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 23, 43, 5, 8, 9, 'made a man every whit whole', 'Sabbath Healing Connection', 'Both passages emphasize healing on the Sabbath. In John 5:8-9, Jesus heals a man, while in John 7:23, He discusses the importance of doing good on the Sabbath, highlighting the tension between the law and acts of compassion.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 24, 23, 11, 3, 4, 'judge not according to the appearance', 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteous judgment in both passages. John 7:24 emphasizes not judging by appearances, while Isaiah 11:3-4 states that true judgment does not rely on sight or hearing but is rooted in righteousness.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 24, 59, 2, 9, 9, 'judge righteous judgment', 'Judgment and Respect in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and the importance of not making superficial assessments. Both passages emphasize the need for righteous judgment and warn against showing favoritism, which leads to sin.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 24, 43, 8, 15, 15, 'judge not according to the appearance', 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the nature of judgment. John 7:24 warns against judging appearances, while John 8:15 highlights judging ''after the flesh,'' suggesting a contrast between superficial and righteous judgment.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 24, 20, 17, 15, 15, 'judge righteous judgment', 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of righteous judgment. John 7:24 warns against judging by appearance, while Proverbs 17:15 condemns justifying the wicked and condemning the just, highlighting the necessity of discernment in judgment.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 24, 20, 24, 23, 23, 'judge righteous judgment', 'Judgment and Impartiality', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of righteous judgment without bias. John 7:24 warns against judging by appearance, while Proverbs 24:23 cautions against having respect of persons in judgment.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 24, 59, 2, 1, 1, 'judge not according to the appearance', 'Judgment and Respect for Persons', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and the importance of not making superficial assessments based on appearances. Both passages emphasize the need for righteous judgment and warn against favoritism or respect of persons.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 24, 3, 19, 15, 15, 'judge righteous judgment', 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of judging righteously without bias. John 7:24 warns against judging by appearance, while Leviticus 19:15 instructs to avoid favoritism in judgment. This connection highlights a consistent biblical theme of fairness in judgment.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 25, 43, 7, 10, 11, 'they seek to kill', 'Seeking Jesus at the Feast', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of people seeking Jesus during the feast. In John 7:10-11, the Jews are actively looking for him, while in John 7:25, some question if he is the one they seek to kill.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 26, 43, 7, 48, 48, 'rulers know indeed that this is the very Christ', 'Rulers'' Response to Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the rulers'' silence and disbelief regarding Jesus. The first verse questions whether the rulers recognize him as the Christ, while the second directly asks if any rulers have believed in him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 26, 55, 1, 7, 8, 'speaketh boldly', 'Courage in Testimony', 'This connection highlights the theme of boldness in proclaiming faith. Both passages emphasize the importance of not being ashamed and speaking boldly about one''s beliefs.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 26, 19, 40, 9, 10, 'lo, he speaketh boldly', 'Bold Declaration of Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of bold proclamation. Both passages emphasize the act of declaring righteousness and truth in a public setting.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 26, 19, 71, 15, 16, 'speaketh boldly', 'Boldness in Proclamation', 'This connection highlights the theme of boldly proclaiming righteousness and salvation. Both passages emphasize speaking out about God''s righteousness and the identity of Christ.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 26, 20, 28, 1, 1, 'speaketh boldly', 'Boldness of the Righteous', 'This connection highlights the theme of boldness in both passages. In John 7:26, the speaker''s boldness is noted, while Proverbs 28:1 states that the righteous are ''bold as a lion.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 26, 23, 42, 4, 4, 'speaketh boldly', 'Judgment and Boldness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of boldness in proclaiming judgment. In John 7:26, the boldness of the speaker suggests a significant authority, while Isaiah 42:4 emphasizes the establishment of judgment in the earth.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 26, 23, 50, 7, 8, 'speaketh boldly', 'Boldness and Justification', 'This connection highlights the theme of boldness in both passages. In John 7:26, the speaker''s boldness is noted, while Isaiah 50:7 emphasizes confidence in God''s support and justification.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 27, 33, 5, 2, 2, 'when Christ cometh, no man knoweth whence he is', 'Connection of Christ''s Origin', 'This connection highlights the mystery surrounding the origins of the Messiah. John 7:27 mentions uncertainty about Christ''s origins, while Micah 5:2 specifies Bethlehem as the birthplace of the ruler in Israel.', 'prophecy', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 27, 43, 7, 41, 42, 'no man knoweth whence he is', 'Identity of the Christ', 'This connection highlights the confusion about Jesus'' origins. Both passages emphasize the debate regarding whether the Christ can come from Galilee, contrasting with the expectation of his lineage from Bethlehem and David.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 27, 43, 6, 42, 42, 'we know this man whence he is', 'Identity of Jesus and Origins', 'Both passages emphasize the question of Jesus'' origins. In John 7:27, the crowd acknowledges their knowledge of Jesus'' earthly background, while in John 6:42, they express confusion about his claim of divine descent. This connection highlights the tension between his known identity and his heavenly origin.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 27, 40, 13, 54, 57, NULL, 'Recognition of Jesus'' Origins', 'Both passages emphasize the question of Jesus'' origins and wisdom. In John, the crowd expresses confusion about Christ''s identity, while in Matthew, the people question how Jesus, known as the carpenter''s son, possesses such wisdom and power.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 27, 24, 30, 21, 21, 'when Christ cometh, no man knoweth whence he is', 'Connection of Unknown Origins', 'Both passages emphasize the mystery surrounding the origins of the leader. John 7:27 mentions that no one knows where Christ comes from, while Jeremiah 30:21 speaks of a governor who will arise from among the people, suggesting a divine selection that is not immediately apparent.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 27, 41, 6, 3, 3, 'this man whence he is', 'Identity of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the recognition of Jesus'' earthly origins. In John 7:27, there is a question about knowing where the Christ comes from, while Mark 6:3 highlights Jesus'' familiar background as a carpenter and son of Mary.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 27, 23, 11, 1, 1, 'when Christ cometh, no man knoweth whence he is', 'Messianic Identity Connection', 'This connection highlights the mystery surrounding the Messiah''s origins. John 7:27 mentions uncertainty about where Christ comes from, while Isaiah 11:1 prophesies the emergence of a significant figure from Jesse''s lineage.', 'prophecy', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
